Date:  0/0/1986
Source:  NZ Pocket Oxford Dictionary
Author:
Vol / Page:  176
Edition:
Quote:  <i>crook ... 3 a. NZ & Austral</i>. ill, out of sorts (<i>John felt pretty crook</i>); (of thing) unsatisfactory, out of order <i>(things went crook from the beginning, the engine sounds crook to me). 4. go crook (at) NZ & Austral</i>. be angry (with), speak angrily (to).
